quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  77,46,"(O you disbelievers)! Eat and enjoy yourselves (in this worldly life) for a little while. Verily, you are the Mujrimûn (polytheists, disbelievers, sinners, criminals)."
  77,47,"Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)!"
  77,48,"And when it is said to them: ",footnotes:1:[{77:48}]
  79,37,"Then for him who transgressed all bounds, (in disbelief, oppression and evil deeds of disobedience to Allâh)."
  79,38,"And preferred the life of this world (by following his evil desires and lusts),"
  79,39,"Verily, his abode will be Hell-fire;"
  80,34,"That Day shall a man flee from his brother,"
  80,35,"And from his mother and his father,"
  80,36,"And from his wife and his children."
  83,22,"Verily, Al-Abrâr (the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism) will be in Delight (Paradise)."
  83,23,"On thrones, looking (at all things)."
  83,24,"You will recognise in their faces the brightness of delight."
  84,19,"You shall certainly travel from stage to stage (in this life and in the Hereafter)."
  84,20,"What is the matter with them, that they believe not?"
  84,21,"And when the Qur’ân is recited to them, they fall not prostrate."
  85,16,"(He is the) Doer of whatsoever He intends (or wills)."
  85,17,"Has the story reached you of the hosts,"
  85,18,"Of Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) and Thamûd?"
  86,10,"Then he will have no power, nor any helper."
  86,11,"By the sky (having rain clouds) which gives rain, again and again."
  86,12,"And the earth which splits (with the growth of trees and plants)."
  87,7,"Except what Allâh may will. He knows what is apparent and what is hidden."
  87,8,"And We shall make easy for you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) the easy way (i.e. the doing of righteous deeds)."
  87,9,"Therefore remind (men) in case the reminder profits (them)."
  88,4,"They will enter in the hot blazing Fire."
  88,5,"They will be given to drink from a boiling spring,"
  88,6,"No food will there be for them but a poisonous thorny plant,"
  89,1,"By the dawn;"
  89,2,"By the ten nights (i.e. the first ten days of the month of Dhul-Hijjah){1},",footnotes:1:[{89:2} Narrated Ibn ‘Abbâs رضي الله عنهما: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "No good deeds done on other days are superior to those done on these (first ten days of Dhul-Hijjah)." Then some Companions of the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "Not even Jihâd ?" He replied, "Not even Jihâd, except that of a man who does it by putting himself and his property in danger (for Allâh’s sake) and does not return with any of those things." (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.2, Hadith No.86).]
  89,3,"And by the even and the odd (of all the creations of Allâh).{1}",footnotes:1:[{89:3} "Even" and "Odd" is interpreted differently by different religious scholars. Some say: Even is the Day of Slaughtering of the Sacrifices, i.e. 10th of Dhul-Hijjah, and Odd is the Day of ‘Arafah (Hajj ), i.e. 9th of Dhul-Hijjah. Others say: Even is all the creatures and Odd is Allâh. Some say it is the compulsory congregational prayer, i.e. Maghrib is Witr , and the other four prayers are Shaf‘]
